<subSubSection id="A2BE6A3C6BC7C25928E74A30F218C115" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="28DF02DA0D33DB295C18C2FC3D4A668C" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CCFA24F22F515B0BD5C0ABD96D2F4ED2" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">This species was collected in flower and fruit in May.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F7A55F5FB3EFEB3A403A43400870E549" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4380837A147FAC4ED339E0BAAAA8FFE8" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B1869188BFB9ED5B5F442F3DB3EBE10" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7EA921E29ACE05D327957BA7576E5492" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Distribution of Miconia phyrnosomaderma (open star), Miconia limoides (open circles), and Miconia paralimoides (closed circles)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.72.9355.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106477" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">23</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BAD961B7AECD7E18808D257D72E64E81" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia phrynosomaderma" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phrynosomaderma">
<emphasis id="227F43CDD1B07909B7A393C64AB3C05A" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia phrynosomaderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the Massif du Nord, at Morne Belle Terre, Departement du Artibonite, Haiti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C75306CB044060A9FAD23ABB24E6030E" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="D7BB275CB64E9D8234CD74E8D599FB9C" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91533A1C536CFDF9DD63CEA247AFFB89" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">This species occurs on metamorphic rock at 1050 m elevation, but no information regarding plant community is available.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="466BC7354DDDF4F847BAF3598B97A23A" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="E39EAE4D827C5E7A890B916F75EC21F4" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="681403D3BB2E353A7C95655B21290B22" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="A22AD57D57A92E4C595C1DB981BB6470" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia phrynosomaderma" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phrynosomaderma">
<emphasis id="4F0DC20E2223BF77C7815FE650CB75CA" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia phrynosomaderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely endangered due to the intense pressure from habitat destruction, as a result of current subsistence farming practices and charcoal production in the Massif du Norde, Haiti. However, there is insufficient data to determine actual conservation status of the species. Thus we categorize the species as data deficient.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="849C82B0E9F502B93928863A81499A24" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="896C24C00DC5520807A89126D91182CC" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D033BAF3C72ACBD8A90561143ED3436" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="BC75155418295DD8E6D9FB45A0DC79E6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia phrynosomaderma" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phrynosomaderma">
<emphasis id="3217868CAA96EBF1D7C25B1299799BBA" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia phrynosomaderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="9C157FC317E70943CFFCC120DA8FD33F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia limoides" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limoides">
<emphasis id="7061D433B4D35AF4F7DF560B84E5893C" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia limoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shares the descending stem hairs with upwardly recurved apices, as well as leaf shape (broadly elliptical; Figs 
<figureCitation id="8EC7B109A7E2B8057A9A8C47BEC9AEFB" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Miconia lima. A habit (Ekman H 1635) B flower (Judd 6587) C petal side view (Clase 935) D petal adaxial surface (Judd 6587) E stamen (Howard 12300) F fruit longitudinal section (Judd 5172) G fruit (Holdridge 1404) H seed (Judd 5172)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.72.9355.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106471" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2A789EC7AAF3F6533A786B7E9FA6B778" captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Illustration of Miconia paralimoides. A habit (Veloz 4059) B close-up of upper leaf surface (Garcia 1186) C close-up of lower leaf surface (Garcia 1186) D flower Veloz 4059) E petal abaxial surface (Veloz 4059) F petal adaxial surface (Veloz 4059) G stamen (Veloz 4059) H fruit longitudinal section (F. Jimenez 176 - A). Reproduced with permission from Majure and Judd (2013 b)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.72.9355.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106480" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">26D</figureCitation>
). However, the two species differ in ad- and abaxial leaf surface indumentum, as well as petal base (clawed in 
<taxonomicName id="9941B7A115E491A2E57B932335BA9659" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia phrynosomaderma" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phrynosomaderma">
<emphasis id="60BD2F9BF11E13152B81287AAD2D6A21" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia phrynosomaderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. non-clawed in 
<taxonomicName id="92AF1592EBE0924EBDD9D96DF7CEE12E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia limoides" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limoides">
<emphasis id="91183286EBB5E3446EC8C29A815C1926" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia limoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), calyx teeth length (2.2-3.3 vs. 1.5-2.1 in 
<taxonomicName id="F164D5AC2FC5E2D878429F5B7EB3FFE1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia limoides" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limoides">
<emphasis id="95FFD29D4C581BAA121D27B9916076B9" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia limoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the presence of a dorso-basal anther appendage in 
<taxonomicName id="73BFC6ED0A6D0001CCE0EC1FE81D88CE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia phrynosomaderma" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phrynosomaderma">
<emphasis id="EE4928428247857520C8220001F9CED4" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia phrynosomaderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(to 0.3 mm long vs. only to 0.1 mm long in 
<taxonomicName id="46FD679D4220D90A9CC548A4E253034B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia limoides" order="Myrtales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limoides">
<emphasis id="C0D867ADC0011617BF64BCAE044B82C8" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Miconia limoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0445B3B43747481CDCAD39818FFED5B9" author="Majure, LC" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="265 - 274" refId="B38" refString="Majure, LC, Judd, WS, 2013a. Miconia phrynosomaderma (Melastomataceae: Miconieae), a new species from the Massif du Nord, Haiti, and sixteen new names and combinations. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 7: 265 - 274" title="Miconia phrynosomaderma (Melastomataceae: Miconieae), a new species from the Massif du Nord, Haiti, and sixteen new names and combinations." volume="7" year="2013 a">Majure and Judd 2013a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
